## Service responsibilities

Each service owns exactly one domain:

- `llm_service.py` — all LLM provider calls (stream + structured)
- `rag_service.py` — context assembly, chunking, embedding, pgvector search
- `drift_service.py` — Work Order staleness detection
- `conflict_service.py` — section pair conflict/gap analysis
- `graph_service.py` — knowledge graph edge management
- `publish_service.py` — spec compilation, git commit, trigger analysis
- `git_service.py` — GitLab API calls only

## Cross-service calls

Services may call other services but must not import routers or models directly.
Pass dependencies via constructor injection — never import a service as a singleton.

## Token tracking

Every `LLMService` call automatically records token usage via `TokenTracker`.
Do not add manual token counting anywhere else.

## RAG context budget

Default token budget is 6000. Do not exceed this without explicit justification.
The overflow fallback order is:

1. Summarise Software Definition if > 500 tokens
2. Truncate the current section from the bottom — preserve at least the first 20% (opening context is highest priority)
3. Show the UI warning banner if mandatory context still exceeds budget after steps 1–2 — see `docs/atelier-functional-requirements.md` (Smart Context Assembly / overflow fallback)
4. The LLM call always proceeds — never block silently
